SWEDISH: Det finns föremål som måste tas bort från möbelns byggområde innan det kan utvecklas.

NOTES: E.g. “Waiting for more wooden planks to be available”

For when a crop plant is infested with insects and other pests and needs some work to remove them

ENGLISH: This crop has been afflicted by an excessive number of aphids and other insects which need to be removed by a {{PROFESSION.FARMER}} before it can flourish again. Not removing the pests in time could mean that this crop dies!
SWEDISH: Denna gröda har drabbats av ett alltför stort antal bladlöss och andra insekter som måste avlägsnas av en {{PROFER.FARMER}} innan den kan blomstra igen. Att inte ta bort skadedjur i tid kan innebära att denna gröda dör!

NOTES: E.g. “Progress towards harvest: 30%”

ENGLISH: This plant has no access to water for a long time and has stopped growing
This plant has not been watered and is growing slowly
You can irrigate your crops with a channel containing water with 2 tiles.
This plant has been watered recently and is growing quickly

ENGLISH: Destroyed by prolonged exposure to rain
Irrigation channels provide access to water to crops within 2 tiles. Build a water pump and connect the channels to it using pipes.

NOTES: Used when the player clicks on an area they have not discovered yet
This is a made-up fantasy food

ENGLISH: This is an infamously tough bread which is so hard and practically inedible that it takes a very long time to turn mouldy. The human explorer J. A. Moffatt once described eating it as “akin to chewing gravel that has been dredged from a swamp”. Fortunately most dwarves don’t seem to mind.
SWEDISH: Detta är ett skamligt tufft bröd som är så svårt och praktiskt oätligt att det tar mycket lång tid att bli mögligt. Den mänskliga upptäcktsresanden J. A. Moffatt beskrev en gång att äta den som ”besläktad med att tugga grus som har muddrats från ett träsk”. Lyckligtvis verkar de flesta dvärgar inte bry sig.

NOTES: Actually just to describe “wheat” as a foodstuff, not specifically bread

ENGLISH: Fuel is required in the production of metal, both by the {{FURNITURE.BLOOMERY_FURNACE}} and the {{FURNITURE.FORGE}}.
SWEDISH: Bränsle krävs vid tillverkning av metall, både av {{FEBURITURE.BLOOMERY_UGE}} och {{FURNITURE.FORGE}}.

ENGLISH: Military settlers will practice their ranged combat skills here up to level 50.
A crafting station for intricate items produced by an {{PROFESSION.ARTISAN}}.
A {{PROFESSION.CHEF}} works here to turn {{RESOURCE.FLOUR.SACK.PLURAL}} into {{INGREDIENT.DOUGH}}.
SWEDISH: A {{PROCESS.CHEF}} fungerar här för att förvandla {{RESOURCE.FLOUR.SACK.PLURAL}} till {{INDERENT.DEG}}.

NOTES: For the baking of bread

ENGLISH: A {{PROFESSION.CHEF}} bakes loaves here using prepared {{INGREDIENT.DOUGH}}.
SWEDISH: En {{PROCISC.CHEF}} bakar bröd här med hjälp av preparerade {{INDERENT.DEG}}.

ENGLISH: A beer barrel is on the way
This is where fermented {{LIQUID.BEER}} is served from.

NOTES: A simple type of furnace to smelt metal from ore

ENGLISH: A {{PROFESSION.BLACKSMITH}} uses this hand-operated furnace to turn {{RESOURCE.ORE.CRUSHED.PLURAL}} and {{FUEL.SACK}} into {{MATERIAL_TYPE.METAL.ADJECTIVE}} {{RESOURCE.METAL.INGOT.PLURAL}}.
SWEDISH: En {{PROFESSI.BLAKSMITH}} använder denna handdrivna ugn för att omvandla {{RESOURCE.ORE.CRUSHED.PLURAL}} och {FUEL.SACK}} till {{MATERIAL_TYPE.METAL.INGOT.PLURAL}}.

ENGLISH: This is used to construct items out of bone.
This is used to produce the final wort (unfermented beer) using {{VEGETABLE.HOPS}} and wort from the {{FURNITURE.MASH_TUN}}.
Fish and animal carcasses are prepared here into usable meat.
Most wooden items and tools are produced here, such as {{PRODUCT.BUCKET.PLURAL}} and {{PRODUCT.BARREL.PLURAL}}.
SWEDISH: De flesta träartiklar och verktyg produceras här, till exempel {{PRODUCT.BOCKET.PLURAL} och {{PRODUCT.BARREL.PLURAL}}.

NOTES: A large metal pot for cooking (common with Halloween)

ENGLISH: A cauldron is used to serve a large quantity of soup to hungry settlers. The soup is produced in a {{ROOMS.KITCHEN}} before being moved to a {{ROOMS.FEASTING_HALL}} for serving.
SWEDISH: En kittel används för att servera en stor mängd soppa till hungriga bosättare. Soppan produceras i en {{ROOMS.CITY}} innan den flyttas till en {{ROOPS.FEASTING_HALL}} för servering.

ENGLISH: Settlers can sit here while using the {{FURNITURE.FEASTING_TABLE}}.
This is a pile of {{RESOURCE.LOGS.PLURAL}} covered with {{MATERIAL_TYPE.EARTH}} and slowly burned to produce {{ORE.CHARCOAL.NOUN}}, which can then be used as {{FUEL.SACK}}.
SWEDISH: Detta är en hög med {{RESOURCE.LOGS.PLURAL}} täckt med {{MATERIAL_TYPE.EARD}} och långsamt brändes för att producera {{ORE.CHARCOAL.NOUN}}, som sedan kan användas som {FUEL.SACK}}.

ENGLISH: A coke oven converts {{ORE.BITUMINOUS_COAL.NOUN}} into {{ORE.COKE.NOUN}} so that it can be used as {{FUEL.SACK}}.
SWEDISH: En koksugn omvandlar {{ORE.BITUMINOUS_COAL.NOUN}} till {{ORE.COKE.NOUN}} så att den kan användas som {{FUEL.SACK}}.

NOTES: E.g. “Granite stonemason workbench”

ENGLISH: Waiting to be injected with mushroom spawn
SWEDISH: Väntar på att injiceras med svampspawn

ENGLISH: Dough can be taken from {{FURNITURE.BAKERS_WORKTOP}} to store here before entering the {{FURNITURE.BAKING_OVEN}}.
Use this to determine which items to export from the room.

NOTES: A very large table for a feast

ENGLISH: With a {{FURNITURE.CHAIR}} in place, your settlers will enjoy their meals at this table.
SWEDISH: Med en {{Furniture.COOR}} på plats, kommer dina nybyggare njuta av sina måltider vid detta bord.

ENGLISH: This is where {{LIQUID.HOPPED_WORT}} is fermented into {{LIQUID.BEER}}.
Neatly store away your caught fish for future cooking.
This is a crafting station for ranged weapons and ammunition.

NOTES: This is a table with a hand-operated flour mill stone on top

ENGLISH: The gristmill grinds {{VEGETABLE.WHEAT}} into {{RESOURCE.FLOUR.SACK.NOUN}} so that it can be used by a {{PROFESSION.CHEF}}.
SWEDISH: Gristmill malar {{VEETABL.VETE}} i {{RESOURCE.FLOUR.SACK.NOUN}} så att den kan användas av en {{PROCESTI.CHEF}}.

ENGLISH: This is where a {{PROFESSION.BLACKSMITH}} works with {{MATERIAL_TYPE.METAL.ADJECTIVE}} {{RESOURCE.METAL.INGOT.PLURAL}} and {{FUEL.SACK}} to craft items and weapons.
SWEDISH: Här arbetar en {{PROCESS.BLAKSMITH}} med {{MATERIAL_TYPE.METAL.ADJECTIVE} {RESOURCE.METAL.INGOT.PLURAL}} och {FUEL.SACK}} för att tillverka föremål och vapen.

ENGLISH: A hastily-dug grave for deceased settlers that can only be dug into {{MATERIAL_TYPE.EARTH}}.
SWEDISH: En hastigt grävd grav för avlidna bosättare som endast kan placeras i {{MATERIAL_TYPE.EARD}}.

ENGLISH: Visiting merchants will park their wagons here.
Use this to determine which items to import to the room.

NOTES: Simple piece of furniture in a kitchen used to hold ingredients on top of it

ENGLISH: An area to store ingredients for a {{PROFESSION.CHEF}} to cook soup.
SWEDISH: Ett område för att lagra ingredienser för en {{PROCUS.CHEF}} för att laga soppa.

ENGLISH: A lantern provides light. This does not currently have an in-game effect.
SWEDISH: En lykta ger ljus — detta har för närvarande ingen effekt i spelet.

ENGLISH: A workbench to produce leather goods like armour and waterskins.
A landmark for the {{ROOMS.TRADING_DEPOT}}. This does not currently have an in-game effect.
Used to craft textiles such as {{PRODUCT.LINEN.NOUN}} from {{RESOURCE.HEMP.FIBRE.BUNDLE.PLURAL}}.
Here brewers steep barley and then dry it out using a kiln to produce malt.
This is used to produce wort (unfermented beer) from milled malt and water.
A log that has been injected with {{INGREDIENT.MUSHROOM.SPAWN.PLURAL}} to produce several harvests of delicious, juicy mushrooms.
SWEDISH: En logg som injicerats med {{INDERENENT.MUSTOM.SPAWN.PLURAL}} för att producera flera skördar av läckra, saftiga svampar.

NOTES: This is a trough of water used to immerse mushroom logs in for a period of time

ENGLISH: After innoculation, a {{FURNITURE.MUSHROOM_LOG}} is placed in this tank to “shock” the mushroom colony and encourage it to grow mushrooms.
SWEDISH: Efter oskulation placeras en {{FEBRUARIET.MUSTOM_LOG}} i denna tank för att ”chocka” svampkolonin och uppmuntra den att odla svamp.

ENGLISH: Raw {{RESOURCE.ORE.UNREFINED.PLURAL}} is crushed to a more workable size so that it can be used in a {{FURNITURE.BLOOMERY_FURNACE}}.
SWEDISH: Raw {RESOURCE.ORE.UNREFERED.PLURAL}} är krossad till en mer användbar storlek så att den kan användas i {{FURCE.BLOOMERY_UGE}}.

NOTES: A pillar used to support a roof

ENGLISH: A pillar is required to stop large mined-out areas from collapsing. An area of 7x7 tiles that have been mined without any pillars or other supports in place will eventually collapse.
SWEDISH: En pelare krävs för att stoppa stora utvinda områden från att kollapsa. Ett område med 7x7 plattor som har utvinns utan några pelare eller andra stöd på plats kommer så småningom att kollapsa.

ENGLISH: This is used to process raw {{VEGETABLE.HEMP}} into hemp fibre that can be worked into useful materials.

NOTES: A stone tomb

ENGLISH: This elaborate stone container is the final resting place of a deceased settler.
SWEDISH: Denna genomarbetade stenbehållare är den sista viloplatsen för en avliden bosättare.

NOTES: A table used to hold food for serving

ENGLISH: {{PRODUCT.BREAD.LOAF.PLURAL}} are placed here for serving after being baked in a {{FURNITURE.BAKING_OVEN}}.
SWEDISH: {{PRODUCT.BREAD.LOAF.PLURAL}} är placerade här för servering efter att ha bakats i en {{FURNITURE.BAKING_OVN}}.

ENGLISH: A bed is the best place for a comfortable night’s rest.
SWEDISH: En säng är den bästa platsen för en bekväm natts vila.

ENGLISH: Your settlers will use this space to sleep on the floor. Not very comfortable!
A decorative banner to denote the trading depot.
Military settlers will practice their melee combat skills here up to level 50.
Provides mechanical power to other contraptions via {{PRODUCT.STONE.GEAR.PLURAL}} and shafts. Must be built adjacent to a river.
A water barrel is a place for your settlers to get a thirst-quenching drink, rather than having to find a natural water source like the river.
SWEDISH: Ett vattenfat är en plats för dina nybyggare att få en törstsläckande dryck, snarare än att behöva hitta en naturlig vattenkälla som floden.

ENGLISH: Moves water from the river to a pipe system.
A well provides a source of water, but must be connected to a working pipe system.
Provides mechanical power to other contraptions via {{PRODUCT.STONE.GEAR.PLURAL}} and shafts.
A {{PROFESSION.WOODCUTTER}} works here to turn {{RESOURCE.LOGS.PLURAL}} into {{RESOURCE.PLANKS.PLURAL}}.
SWEDISH: A {{PROCESS.WOOKCUTER}} fungerar här för att förvandla {{RESOURCE.LOGS.PLURAL}} till {{RESOURCE.PLURAL}}.

ENGLISH: A violet-hued variety of quartz. Ancient humans believed it could magically protect them from becoming too drunk. For this reason it is not very popular in dwarven culture.
SWEDISH: En violett-hued sort av kvarts. Forntida människor trodde att det kunde skydda dem från att bli för fulla. Av denna anledning är det inte särskilt populärt i dvärgkultur.

ENGLISH: An opal-like gemstone which has a red to green iridescence. It is known as the “hunting stone” and amulets made from it are meant to bring good luck to a hunt.
SWEDISH: En opalliknande ädelsten som har en röd till grön iridescens. Det är känt som ”jaktsten” och amuletter gjorda av den är avsedda att bringa lycka till en jakt.

ENGLISH: A cyan-coloured variety of beryl. Some humans believe it offers magical protection against the dangers of the seas. This is because an ancient mage used a combination of sky and ice magic to protect trading ships during the age of darkness.
SWEDISH: En cyanfärgad sort av beryl. Vissa människor tror att det erbjuder magiskt skydd mot farorna i haven. Detta beror på att en uråldrig magiker använde en kombination av himmel och is magi för att skydda handelsfartyg under mörkrets tid.

ENGLISH: Also known as red beryl, it is a very rare gemstone. It is often confused for a red-coloured emerald.
SWEDISH: Även känd som röd beryl, det är en mycket sällsynt ädelsten. Det är ofta förvirrad för en rödfärgad smaragd.

ENGLISH: An ore of mercury which is often used in jewellery due to its deep-red hue. It is also used to produce the dye known as vermillion.
SWEDISH: En kvicksilvermalm som ofta används i smycken på grund av sin djupröda nyans. Det används också för att producera färgämnet som kallas vermillion.

ENGLISH: A yellowish variety of quartz. It is the gemstone most similar in colour to gold, so most dwarves think citrine is lucky.
SWEDISH: En gulaktig sort av kvarts. Det är ädelstenen som är mest lik guld, så de flesta dvärgar tycker att citrin har tur.

ENGLISH: The hardest known material and one of the most important of the seven heavenly stones. Diamonds are the most condensed form of the neutral element known as “spirit” or “aether”.
SWEDISH: Det svåraste kända materialet och en av de viktigaste av de sju himmelska stenarna. Diamanter är den mest kondenserade formen av det neutrala elementet som kallas ”ande” eller ”eter”.

ENGLISH: A vibrant green variety of beryl. It is thought that engraving on an emerald brings great misfortune. Emeralds are closely related to elemental life and associated magic.
SWEDISH: En livfull grön variation av beryl. Man tror att gravyr på en smaragd ger stor olycka. Smaragder är nära besläktade med elementärt liv och tillhörande magi.

ENGLISH: Garnets cover a variety of minerals used as gemstones, all with a deep red colour. Some garnet gems are actually a condensed form of elemental fire.
SWEDISH: Granat täcker en mängd mineraler som används som ädelstenar, alla med en djup röd färg. Vissa granatpärlor är faktiskt en kondenserad form av elementär eld.

ENGLISH: A mineral with a light-green colour often used for decoration. Also, elves have been known to use jade to produce medicine which can cure ailments of the gut.
SWEDISH: Ett mineral med ljusgrön färg som ofta används för dekoration. Dessutom har alver varit kända för att använda jade för att producera medicin som kan bota sjukdomar i tarmen.

ENGLISH: An impure variety of silica which can occur in several colours, but most commonly red. Jasper is favoured as a decoration material by orcs due to its variety.
SWEDISH: En oren sort av kiseldioxid som kan förekomma i flera färger, men oftast röd. Jasper gynnas som dekorationsmaterial av orcher på grund av dess mångfald.

ENGLISH: A rock which shines with a typically light-blue iridescence. Rarer specimens can reflect a wide range of colours.
SWEDISH: En sten som lyser med en typiskt ljusblå iridescens. Sällare exemplar kan spegla ett brett spektrum av färger.

ENGLISH: A rock with a brilliant deep blue hue which is used as a precious stone.
SWEDISH: En sten med en lysande djupblå nyans som används som en ädelsten.

ENGLISH: A mineral which can be polished into beads for use in jewellery. These beads can by dyed into many different colours.
SWEDISH: Ett mineral som kan poleras till pärlor för användning i smycken. Dessa pärlor kan färgas i många olika färger.

ENGLISH: Thought to be formed by moonlight captured in rock, which makes this gemstone a favourite of the elves.
SWEDISH: Trodde bildas av månskenet fångat i sten, vilket gör denna ädelsten till en favorit bland alverna.

ENGLISH: A rose-coloured variety of beryl. It was named after being popularised by a particularly wealthy merchant in the age of myth.
SWEDISH: En rosafärgad sort av beryl. Det namngavs efter att ha blivit populär av en särskilt rik köpman i mytens tidsålder.

ENGLISH: A form of silica infused with the magic of the oceans, which makes this a favourite of sailors and fishermen.
SWEDISH: En form av kiseldioxid fylld med havens magi, vilket gör detta till en favorit bland sjömän och fiskare.

ENGLISH: A very rare gemstone which is often identified as an off-colour sapphire. The crystals are naturally hexagonal in shape and a favourite of tacticians.
SWEDISH: En mycket sällsynt ädelsten som ofta identifieras som en ofärgad safir. Kristallerna är naturligt sexkantiga i form och en favorit hos taktiker.

ENGLISH: Found in varying shades of red to pink. It is not as hard as most gemstones making it a poor choice for rings and other high-impact jewellery.
SWEDISH: Finns i olika nyanser av rött till rosa. Det är inte lika svårt som de flesta ädelstenar, vilket gör det till ett dåligt val för ringar och andra stora smycken.

ENGLISH: The purest form of quartz. Rock crystals often feature in magical artifacts as they are a condensed form of the element of ice.
SWEDISH: Den renaste formen av kvarts. Stenkristaller förekommer ofta i magiska artefakter eftersom de är en kondenserad form av iselementet.

ENGLISH: One of the seven heavenly stones, rubies are the element of fire condensed into a solid form.
SWEDISH: En av de sju himmelska stenarna, rubiner är eldens element kondenserad till en fast form.

ENGLISH: Often believed to protect the wearer from the attention of daemons, sapphires are much sought-after by mages for use in sky and air-based magic.
SWEDISH: Ofta tros skydda bäraren från demonernas uppmärksamhet, safirer är mycket eftertraktade av magiker för användning i himlen och luftbaserad magi.

ENGLISH: Often confused with heavenly stones like true rubies and sapphires, spinels are a lesser form of magic-infused gem which can be associated with any of the elements, depending on colour.
SWEDISH: Ofta förväxlas med himmelska stenar som äkta rubiner och safirer, spineller är en mindre form av magisk infunderad pärla som kan associeras med något av elementen, beroende på färg.

ENGLISH: A rare gemstone that can alternate between blue and violet. It is thought to be formed from the material body of a dead god.
SWEDISH: En sällsynt ädelsten som kan växla mellan blå och violett. Det tros vara bildat av en död guds materiella kropp.

ENGLISH: Sometimes confused with the more common {{GEM.CITRINE.NOUN}} gem, topaz can be found in several colours but most commonly a yellowish brown. It was first discovered on an island which no longer exists.
SWEDISH: Ibland förväxlas med den vanligare ädelstenen {{GEM.CITRINE.NOUN}}, finns topas i flera färger men oftast gulbrun. Den upptäcktes först på en ö som inte längre existerar.

ENGLISH: Often found alongside {{ORE.CASSITERITE.ADJECTIVE}} ore. It is sometimes associated with earth magic.
SWEDISH: Ofta hittas tillsammans med {{ORE.CASSITERITE.ADJEKTIVAL}} malm. Det är ibland förknippat med jordmagi.

ENGLISH: A blue-green mineral often used in decorations. It is thought to bring good luck to the bearer. It is often infused with the element of earth.
SWEDISH: Ett blågrönt mineral som ofta används i dekorationer. Det är tänkt att bringa lycka till bäraren. Det är ofta infunderat med jordens element.

SWEDISH: Spara filen kunde inte laddas eftersom den är inkompatibel med den här versionen av spelet.

SWEDISH: Det var ett oväntat fel när du laddade spelet.

SWEDISH: Den valda språköversättningen är för närvarande ofullständig och kommer att sakna en del text. Ett reservspråk kommer att användas.

SWEDISH: En eller flera mods är inkompatibla med den här versionen av spelet och har avaktiverats. Du kan söka efter uppdateringar i mods-menyn.

SWEDISH: Du måste starta om spelet för att ändringen ska träda i kraft

ENGLISH: Make trees transparent when obscuring settlers
SWEDISH: Gör träd genomskinliga när dölja bosättare

SWEDISH: En bro måste täcka båda sidor av floden och vara minst 3x3 plattor i storlek

NOTES: Used to make the game interface larger or smaller

ENGLISH: You can use this view to lay pipes between liquid inputs and outputs, as well as irrigation channels.
These are placed below the ground, so make sure your settlers can access each tile from the side.
Furniture with a liquid input or output display a blue or green icon indicating if they are an input or output to the network.
Use this view to link constructions that require power with mechanisms built from {{PRODUCT.STONE.GEAR.PLURAL}} and shafts.
These are placed below the ground, so make sure your settlers can access each tile from the side.
Constructions which require or produce power will display a red or green icon indicating if they are an input or output to the network.
This view allows you to see which tiles are outside with no roof above them (light blue), and those which have had a roof built overhead (dark brown).
You can use the {{GUI.ROOFING.ADD}} and {{GUI.CANCEL_LABEL}} options to queue up roofing to be constructed, and {{GUI.DECONSTRUCT_LABEL}} to remove any existing roof tiles.
A roof can only be constructed within 3 tiles of a wall or {{FURNITURE.PILLAR}}.
You can use this menu to change the priority of jobs and tasks, so that higher priority jobs will be assigned before lower priority jobs.
While the Priority menu is open, the priority icons are shown in the game world where there is a job or task to be performed, or where a room or item of furniture may create jobs in the future.
Your settlement no longer has an {{TOOL.AXE}} available. You will no longer be able to chop down trees.
More axes can be crafted at the {{FURNITURE.FORGE}}. If you do not have a {{FURNITURE.FORGE}} up and running, you may need to remove a {{FURNITURE.WOODCUTTERS_BENCH}}.
Your settlement no longer has a {{TOOL.CHISEL}} available. This is required to construct stone furniture.
More chisels can be crafted at the {{FURNITURE.FORGE}}. If you do not have a {{FURNITURE.FORGE}} up and running, you may need to remove a {{FURNITURE.STONEMASON_WORKBENCH}}.
Your settlement no longer has a {{TOOL.PLANE}} available. This is required to construct wooden furniture.
More planes can be crafted at the {{FURNITURE.CARPENTRY_WORKBENCH}} from a {{RESOURCE.PLANKS.NOUN}}.
Your settlement no longer has a {{TOOL.SAW}} available. This is required to build a {{FURNITURE.WOODCUTTERS_BENCH}} or {{FURNITURE.CARPENTRY_WORKBENCH}}.

More saws can be crafted at the {{FURNITURE.FORGE}}. If you do not have a {{FURNITURE.FORGE}} up and running, you may need to remove a {{FURNITURE.WOODCUTTERS_BENCH}} or {{FURNITURE.CARPENTRY_WORKBENCH}}.
Use this view to select a type of weapon that the settler will keep in their inventory in case of combat.
It is strongly recommended you assign a ranged weapon such as a {{WEAPON.BOW}} or {{WEAPON.CROSSBOW}} to those settlers assigned as a {{PROFESSION.HUNTER}}.
Weapons which you do not have available are displayed in red.
Click “Tutorial” to be guided through the basics, “Hints only” to skip the tutorial but be provided with info as you play, or “Disable all hints” to stop showing these messages.
Start the game by selecting a location on the map with open space near the river, and clicking the '{{GUI.EMBARK.START}}' button.

NOTES: E.g. “Urist McScrooge, insane dwarf”
E.g. “Urist McScrooge, Dwarven miner”
To be combined with the above as “bread dough”
To be combined with the above as “bread loaf”

ENGLISH: This needs to be milled before it can be used further for brewing.
This is combined with water in a {{FURNITURE.MASH_TUN}} to produce {{LIQUID.WORT}}.
Also known as mycelium, this can be thought of as “seeds” from which to grow mushrooms in a {{ROOMS.MUSHROOM_FARM}}.
SWEDISH: Även känt som mycelium, kan detta ses som ”frön” för att odla svamp i en {{ROOPS.MUSROOM_FARM}}.

NOTES: E.g. “Wheat seed”
E.g. “4 wheat seeds”

ENGLISH: Seeds of the right type are required for planting in a {{ROOMS.FARM}}. They also need to be available in a {{STOCKPILE.GRANARY}} stockpile.
SWEDISH: Frön av rätt typ krävs för plantering i {{ROOMS.FARM}}. De måste också finnas tillgängliga i en {{STOCKPILE.GRANARY}} -lagerlucka.

NOTES: This is the label of “inventory” to go above a list of items contained within a piece of furniture or held by a character
E.g. “2 potatoes”
E.g. “Iron axe”, “Beech wood fishing rod”, “3 marble blocks”
E.g. “2 potatoes”

ENGLISH: This item is terribly made, difficult to use, and would not be worth very much
This item has clearly been made by a master craftsman, it is ideal in every way
This item is poorly made and will slightly impede anyone using it
This item has been crafted with great skill, making it more valuable and easier to use
Beloved by dwarves, this will provide a substantial happiness bonus for a while. The only problem is that they will eventually require it to get through the working day.
This is the final stage of unfermented beer before it is placed in a {{FERMENTATION_TANK}} to produce drinkable beer.
This is unfermented beer, it requires {{VEGETABLE.HOPS}} to be added in a {{FURNITURE.BREW_KETTLE}} for flavour before it can be fermented.
This settler was so unhappy that they have been pushed past the breaking point and will no longer work or even eat!
SWEDISH: Denna bosättare var så olycklig att de har drivit förbi brytpunkten och kommer inte längre att fungera eller ens äta!

NOTES: Used for specifying which material something is made out of
For allowing any kind of material to be used

This is only used as a noun
This isn't actually used in-game yet so won't be combined with other words

Used to make up “Vegetable soup”

ENGLISH: Working very slowly - not enough power
This furniture requires an underground power connection to a power-producer such as a {{FURNITURE.WINDMILL}} or {{FURNITURE.WATERWHEEL}}.
This must be outside to function correctly
This furniture requires an underground power connection to a power-producer such as a {{FURNITURE.WINDMILL}} or {{FURNITURE.WATERWHEEL}}.
Disabled - connect to an underground power connection
This furniture requires an underground power connection - see the {{GUI.BUILD.POWER}} option in the {{GUI.BUILD_LABEL}} menu.
This contraption links up mechanical power in all 4 directions.
A wooden shaft links mechanical power in 2 directions.
Bronze is an alloy of copper and tin. It is harder and much more durable than copper alone. (Alloys have not yet been implemented)
SWEDISH: Brons är en legering av koppar och tenn. Det är svårare och mycket mer hållbart än koppar ensam. (Legeringar har ännu inte genomförts i King under berget)

ENGLISH: As well as occuring naturally as {{ORE.NATIVE_COPPER.NOUN}}, it is also easy to smelt from {{ORE.MALACHITE.NOUN}} ore. Copper has many uses, particularly in coinage, though it is not hard enough to create effective weapons.
SWEDISH: Förutom att den förekommer naturligt som {{ORE.NATIVE_COPPER.NOUN}} är den också lätt att smälta från {{ORE.MALACHITE.NOUN}} malm. Koppar har många användningsområden, särskilt i mynt, men det är inte svårt nog att skapa effektiva vapen.

ENGLISH: The king of metals. Although it is not the rarest or most valuable, gold is the most coveted metal by most races – particularly dwarves.
SWEDISH: Kungen av metaller. Även om det inte är den mest sällsynta eller värdefulla är guld den mest eftertraktade metallen av de flesta raser — särskilt dvärgar.

ENGLISH: It is a poor military which does not have access to iron. Dwarven metalsmiths know the secrets of working this into {{METAL.STEEL.NOUN}}.
SWEDISH: Det är en fattig militär som inte har tillgång till järn. Dvärgmetallsmider känner till hemligheterna bakom att arbeta in detta i {{MEAL.STEEL.NOUN}}.

ENGLISH: A silver-white metal that is highly resistant to corrosion. Platinum is rarer and therefore more valuable than {{METAL.GOLD.NOUN}}.
SWEDISH: En silvervit metall som är mycket motståndskraftig mot korrosion. Platina är ovanligare och därför mer värdefullt än {{MEAL.GOLD.NOUN}}.

ENGLISH: Iron turns to rust when exposed to rain for a long period. Eventually this will decay completely!
Like {{METAL.GOLD.NOUN}}, silver is often used for coinage and as solid bars for the trading of wealth.
SWEDISH: Liksom {{MEAL.GOLD.NOUN}} används silver ofta för mynt och som solida barer för handel med rikedom.

ENGLISH: Far stronger than {{METAL.IRON.NOUN}} which makes for superior weapons and tools, only the dwarves know the secret of creating steel.
SWEDISH: Mycket starkare än {MEAL.IRON.NOUN}} som gör för överlägsna vapen och verktyg, bara dvärgarna känner till hemligheten med att skapa stål.

ENGLISH: Tin can be smelted from {{ORE.CASSITERITE.NOUN}} and alloyed with {{METAL.COPPER.NOUN}} to produce {{METAL.BRONZE.NOUN}}. (Alloys have not yet been implemented)
SWEDISH: Tenn kan smältas från {{ORE.CASSITERITE.NOUN}} och legeras med {{MEAL.COPPER.NOUN}} för att producera {{META.BRONZE.NOUN}}. (Legeringar har ännu inte genomförts i King under berget)

NOTES: Used to assign a squad to active duty during the daytime
Used to assign a squad to active duty during the nighttime

ENGLISH: Please wait while the mod list is being updated. This may take a few minutes.

NOTES: E.g. “Toadstool mushroom”

ENGLISH: Your miners have discovered a new area!
SWEDISH: Dina gruvarbetare har upptäckt ett nytt område!

ENGLISH: A fire has broken out in your settlement!
You have over-fished the river to such an extent that there are no more fish left. You will have to wait until the spawning season next spring for the fish to return.
All things must come to an end. Your settlement lies abandoned.
SWEDISH: Allt måste komma till ett slut. Din bosättning ligger övergiven.

ENGLISH: The prosperity of your settlement has attracted a number of new immigrants to boost your population.
SWEDISH: Välståndet i er bosättning har lockat ett antal nya invandrare för att öka er befolkning.

ENGLISH: A raiding party of orcs has arrived. Prepare yourselves! They will attack after preparing for a while.
An area has caved in due to a lack of pillars and supports.
SWEDISH: Ett område har rasat in på grund av brist på pelare och stöd.

ENGLISH: An item or piece of furniture has been destroyed due to prolonged exposure to rain.\nSome materials such as iron and steel should not be left outside for a long period.
A roof has collapsed due to a lack of pillars and supports.
The gruelling hardship has proven to be too much to handle for {{character}}.
SWEDISH: De hårda svårigheterna har visat sig vara för mycket att hantera för {{character}}.

ENGLISH: {{character}} has become so unhappy that they are throwing a tantrum!
They are heading to your Trading Depot to buy and sell goods.
You must construct a Trading Depot to buy and sell goods.
Bauxite is the primary ore of aluminium. Unfortunately, a means of aluminium production is yet to be discovered.
SWEDISH: Bauxit är den primära malmen av aluminium. Tyvärr har man ännu inte upptäckt ett sätt att tillverka aluminium.

ENGLISH: This can be converted into {{ORE.COKE.NOUN}} using a {{FURNITURE.COKE_OVEN}}.
SWEDISH: Detta kan konverteras till {{ORE.COKE.NOUN}} med hjälp av en {{FURITURE.COKE_OVEN}.

ENGLISH: An ore that can be smelted to produce {{METAL.TIN.NOUN}}.
SWEDISH: En malm som kan smältas för att producera {{METAL.TIN.NOUN}}.

ENGLISH: Often confused with turquoise, it is actually an ore of {{METAL.COPPER}}.
SWEDISH: Ofta förväxlas med turkos, det är faktiskt en malm av {MEAL.COPER}}.

ENGLISH: A refined form of {{ORE.BITUMINOUS_COAL}} which can be used as {{FUEL.SACK}}.
SWEDISH: En raffinerad form av {{ORE.BITUMINOUS_COAL}} som kan användas som {{FUEL.SACK}}.

ENGLISH: An ore that can be smelted to produce {{METAL.SILVER}}.
SWEDISH: En malm som kan smältas för att producera {{MEAL.SILVER}}.

ENGLISH: An ore that can be smelted to produce {{METAL.IRON}}.
SWEDISH: En malm som kan smältas för att producera {{MEAL.Iron}}.

ENGLISH: Ilmenite is the primary ore of titanium. Unfortunately, a means of titanium production is yet to be discovered.
SWEDISH: Ilmenit är den primära malmen av titan. Tyvärr har ett sätt att producera titan ännu inte upptäckts.

ENGLISH: An ore that can be smelted to produce {{METAL.COPPER}}.
SWEDISH: En malm som kan smältas för att producera {{MEAL.COPER}}.

ENGLISH: Naturally-occuring {{METAL.COPPER}} which must be smelted before use.
SWEDISH: Naturligt förekommande {{MEAL.COPER}} som måste smältas före användning.

ENGLISH: Naturally-occuring {{METAL.GOLD}} which must be smelted before use.
SWEDISH: Naturligt förekommande {{MEAL.GOLD}} som måste smältas före användning.

ENGLISH: Naturally-occuring {{METAL.PLATINUM}} which must be smelted before use.
SWEDISH: Naturligt förekommande {{MEAL.PLATINUM}} som måste smältas före användning.

ENGLISH: Naturally-occuring {{METAL.SILVER}} which must be smelted before use.
SWEDISH: Naturligt förekommande {{MEAL.SILVER}} som måste smältas före användning.

ENGLISH: Pollucite is an ore of Caesium, which is currently too dangerous to produce. Particularly crazy dwarven metalsmiths are currently trying to find a reliable method of production.
SWEDISH: Pollusit är en malm av cesium, som för närvarande är för farlig för att producera. Särskilt galna dvärgmetallsmider försöker för närvarande hitta en pålitlig produktionsmetod.

ENGLISH: Also known as Pyrite, its pale-yellow appearance causes some to mistake it for gold. It has several uses when crushed, but care must be taken as it sparks when struck.
SWEDISH: Även känd som Pyrite, orsakar dess blekgula utseende vissa att missta det för guld. Det har flera användningsområden när det krossas, men försiktighet måste tas eftersom det gnistor när det slås.

ENGLISH: A silvery metallic ore which turns black when exposed to air. It is strangely warm to the touch.
SWEDISH: En silverfärgad metallmalm som blir svart när den utsätts för luft. Det är konstigt varmt att ta på.

ENGLISH: A metallic ore which complicates the smelting of tin. It has too high a melting point to be smelted with normal processes.
SWEDISH: En metallisk malm som försvårar smältning av tenn. Den har för hög smältpunkt för att smältas med normala processer.

ENGLISH: • The version of the game client
• The status of the game at the time of the crash
Mountaincore is in active development. To help diagnose and fix bugs, please click "I Accept" below to send anonymous crash reports automatically. \n\nThis is made up of only the following data:
A large block of metal used to hammer heated metal into shape. Required to construct a {{FURNITURE.FORGE}}.
SWEDISH: Ett stort block av metall som används för att hamra uppvärmd metall i form. Krävs för att konstruera en {{FURNITURE.FORGE}.

ENGLISH: Metal hoops used to construct a {{PRODUCT.BARREL.NOUN}}. Also used in some machinery.
SWEDISH: Metallbågar som används för att konstruera en {{PRODUCT.BARREL.NOUN}}. Används även i vissa maskiner.

ENGLISH: Curved wooden planks used to construct a {{PRODUCT.BARREL.NOUN}}.
SWEDISH: Böjda träplankor som används för att konstruera en {{PRODUCT.BARREL.NOUN}}.

ENGLISH: A cylindrical container for liquids. The curved shape makes it easier to roll around.
SWEDISH: En cylindrisk behållare för vätskor. Den krökta formen gör det lättare att rulla runt.

NOTES: A bowl for eating from
E.g. “Bowl of vegetable soup”

ENGLISH: A mix of ingredients that can be baked into {{PRODUCT.BREAD.LOAF.PLURAL}} using an {{FURNITURE.BAKING_OVEN}}.
SWEDISH: En blandning av ingredienser som kan bakas in i {{PRODUCT.BREAD.LOAF.PLURAL}} med hjälp av en {{FURNITURE.BAKING_OVN}}.

NOTES: Translations incorrect and need fixing
Translations incorrect and need fixing

ENGLISH: A small container used to move liquids around by hand.
SWEDISH: En liten behållare som används för att flytta vätskor runt för hand.

NOTES: A large metal pot for cooking (common with Halloween)

ENGLISH: Used by a {{PROFESSION.CHEF}} to prepare soup in a {{ROOMS.KITCHEN}}, where it is then moved to a {{ROOMS.FEASTING_HALL}}.
SWEDISH: Används av en {{PROFESSI.CHEF}} för att tillaga soppa i en {{ROOMS.CITY}}, där den sedan flyttas till en {{ROOMS.FEASTING_HALL}}.

ENGLISH: Used to store coins for trading.
A roll of fabric, primarily used for bedding.
This is a metal container used to store liquids, which must be crafted at the {{FURNITURE.FORGE}}.
Two large stone discs that are ground together to mill harvested crops. Used to construct a {{FURNITURE.FLOUR_MILL}}.
SWEDISH: Två stora stenskivor som är malda tillsammans för att fräs skördade grödor. Används för att konstruera en {{FURITURE.FLOUR_MILL}}.

ENGLISH: A mix of ingredients that can be baked into {{PRODUCT.RATION.LOAF.PLURAL}} using an {{FURNITURE.BAKING_OVEN}}.
These will last a long time to feed your settlers, but you will need other sources of food as a priority.
SWEDISH: Dessa kommer att pågå länge för att mata dina bosättare, men du behöver andra matkällor som en prioritet.

ENGLISH: Used in the construction of mechanisms.
Used for liquids to flow between tiles underground.
Used to connect mechanisms which produce and require power.
Used to connect mechanisms which produce and require power.
Crafts items using metal and also produces metal from ore.
SWEDISH: Hantverk med metall och producerar också metall från malm.

ENGLISH: Prepares all of the food to be consumed by your settlers.
SWEDISH: Förbereder all mat som ska konsumeras av dina nybyggare.

NOTES: This could be “fisherman” and “fisherwoman”

ENGLISH: Catches fish from bodies of water for use as food and resources.
SWEDISH: Fångster fisk från vattenförekomster för användning som livsmedel och resurser.

NOTES: This could be “huntsman” and “huntress”

ENGLISH: Tracks and kills wild animals for their meat and pelts.
SWEDISH: Spår och dödar vilda djur för deras kött och skinn.

ENGLISH: Treats the hides of creatures to produce leather goods.

NOTES: In English at least, “mayoress” is incorrect
Not a fully implemented profession, just used to describe “Milling flour”

SWEDISH: Grävar nya områden med hjälp av en {{TOOL.PICKAXE}}.

ENGLISH: Nobles do not fulfil jobs in the same way as common settlers, but bring fame and prestige to your settlement.
SWEDISH: Adelsmän uppfyller inte jobb på samma sätt som vanliga bosättare, men ger berömmelse och prestige till din bosättning.

NOTES: from “runes” and “blacksmith”
This is an invented term for the game, but should be derived

ENGLISH: Enchants weapons, armour and items with magical runes to boost their abilities.
SWEDISH: Förtrollar vapen, rustningar och föremål med magiska runor för att öka deras förmågor.

ENGLISH: An absolute beginner with little to no experience.
They only understand the basics of their craft.
Though they are becoming skilled, there is still a lot of experience to be earned.
No longer an apprentice, they have reasonable skill in their given craft.
They are well-skilled but still have further heights that can be reached.
Very skilled in their craft, they are now more than competent.
There is little that the expert does not know of their respective field.
Beyond even an expert, they are truly a master of their craft.
There is nobody more skilled in their craft than a grandmaster.
Crafts furniture and items from stone.
SWEDISH: Hantverk möbler och föremål från sten.

ENGLISH: This settler does not have any specific professions and will fulfil any mundane tasks like hauling items.
SWEDISH: Denna bosättare har inga specifika yrken och kommer att uppfylla några vardagliga uppgifter som att transportera föremål.

ENGLISH: Processes materials into clothing and other fabrics.

NOTES: This could be “lumberjack” and “lumberjane”

ENGLISH: Cuts down trees as lumber that can be used in a {{ROOMS.SAWMILL}}.
SWEDISH: Klipper ner träd som virke som kan användas i en {{ROOMS.SAWMILL}}.

ENGLISH: A deer is a non-threatening herbivore which will flee at any sign of danger

NOTES: The male and female forms are only for languages that need them
Note that I'm going with Tolkein's spelling of “dwarves” rather than “dwarfs”

ENGLISH: Dwarves are short and stocky humanoids. They are masters of working with stone and metal. Most dwarves distrust the sky and prefer to stay underground.
SWEDISH: Dvärgar är korta och slitna humanoider. De är mästare på att arbeta med sten och metall. De flesta dvärgar misstror himlen och föredrar att stanna under jorden.

NOTES: Orcs are only male

ENGLISH: Grain that has been milled into a fine powder ready to be used as an ingredient in the production of food.
SWEDISH: Korn som har malts till ett fint pulver redo att användas som ingrediens vid framställning av livsmedel.

ENGLISH: A hunk of rock containing gems ready to be cut and polished.
SWEDISH: En bit sten som innehåller ädelstenar redo att skäras och poleras.

ENGLISH: Sections of a tree that are most commonly prepared into {{RESOURCE.PLANKS.PLURAL}}, but have other uses as well.
SWEDISH: Delar av ett träd som oftast är beredda i {{RESOURCE.PLURC.PLURAL}}, men som också har andra användningsområden.

ENGLISH: A lump of metal mixed with slag which must be hammered into a usable form.
SWEDISH: En klump av metall blandad med slagg som måste hamras i en användbar form.

ENGLISH: Refined metal blocks, ready to be used as a crafting ingredient.
SWEDISH: Raffinerade metallblock, redo att användas som en hantverksingrediens.

ENGLISH: Large, flat plates that are used in some of the larger machinery.
SWEDISH: Stora, platta plattor som används i några av de större maskinerna.

ENGLISH: A log that has been infused with {{INGREDIENT.MUSHROOM.SPAWN.NOUN}}. The body of the log itself is where the mushrooms draw nutrients from. It requires dousing in a {{FURNITURE.MUSHROOM_SHOCK_TANK}} after becoming fully innoculated.
SWEDISH: En logg som har infunderats med {{VERGENT.MUSTOM.SPAWN.NOUN}}. Kroppen i själva loggen är där svampen drar näringsämnen från. Det kräver dousing i en {{FEBRUARIET.MUSTOM_SHOCK_TANK}} efter att ha blivit helt oskulerad.

ENGLISH: Sections of a giant mushroom that can be used in the same way as wooden {{RESOURCE.LOGS.PLURAL}}.
SWEDISH: Sektioner av en jätte svamp som kan användas på samma sätt som trä {{RESOURCE.LOGS.PLURAL}}.

ENGLISH: A metallic sand created by breaking down raw metal ore, ready for use in a {{FURNITURE.BLOOMERY_FURNACE}}.
SWEDISH: En metallisk sand skapad genom att bryta ner råmetallmalm, klar för användning i en {{FURNITURE.BLOOMERY_UGE}}.

ENGLISH: Stone that contains metallic ores which can be processed into usable metal.
SWEDISH: Sten som innehåller metallmalm som kan bearbetas till användbar metall.

ENGLISH: Sections of wood of a fixed size so they can be easily used in constructions and crafting.
SWEDISH: Sektioner av trä av fast storlek så att de enkelt kan användas i konstruktioner och hantverk.

ENGLISH: This mushroom-infused log has been “shocked” in water to encourage the mushrooms to develop and should produce a harvest soon.
SWEDISH: Denna svampinfunderade logg har blivit ”chockad” i vatten för att uppmuntra svampen att utvecklas och bör producera en skörd snart.

ENGLISH: Stone that has been shaped into a cube so that it can be easily used in construction or crafting.
SWEDISH: Sten som har formats till en kub så att den lätt kan användas i konstruktion eller tillverkning.

ENGLISH: A huge piece of stone that must be chiselled into a more useful shape by a {{PROFESSION.STONEMASON}}.
SWEDISH: En stor sten som måste mejslas till en mer användbar form av en {{PROFCTION.STONEMASON}}.

ENGLISH: Sacks of wheat are harvested from farm plots sown with wheat seeds.
Weapons and armour are created here.
Where bread dough is created and then baked into bread.
A place for members of the military to sleep and train.
A place for your settlers to sleep.
SWEDISH: En plats för dina nybyggare att sova. De föredrar att ha individuella sovrum som är minst 9 plattor i storlek, och helst minst 13 plattor i storlek.

ENGLISH: Brews beer for your settlers to enjoy!
Placed across the river to allow access to the other side.
SWEDISH: Placerad tvärs över floden för att ge tillgång till andra sidan.

ENGLISH: This workshop produces most wooden tools and items
SWEDISH: Denna verkstad producerar de flesta träverktyg och föremål.
{{allokerad}} av {{total}} blanksteg som för närvarande används

ENGLISH: Grows crops using {{INGREDIENT.SEEDS.PLURAL}}. Must be placed on {{MATERIAL_TYPE.EARTH.NOUN}}.
SWEDISH: Växer grödor med {{INDERENT.SEEDS.PLURAL}}. Måste placeras på {{MATERIAL_TYPE.EARH.NOUN}}.

ENGLISH: A place for settlers to gather to eat, drink and be merry!
SWEDISH: En plats för nybyggare att samlas för att äta, dricka och vara glada!

ENGLISH: Deceased settlers are laid to rest here.
SWEDISH: Avlidna bosättare läggs för att vila här.

ENGLISH: Most food is prepared here before being served in a {{ROOMS.FEASTING_HALL}}.
SWEDISH: De flesta livsmedel tillagas här innan de serveras i {{ROOPS.FEASTING_HALL}}.

ENGLISH: Craft items out of animal hide.
This workshop produces most items made out of stone.
SWEDISH: Denna verkstad producerar de flesta föremål gjorda av sten.

ENGLISH: Mushrooms can be grown using {{INGREDIENT.MUSHROOM.SPAWN.NOUN}} and wooden {{RESOURCE.LOGS.PLURAL}}.
SWEDISH: Svampar kan odlas med {{EXTRENENENT.MUSTOM.SPAWN.NOUN}} och trä {{RESOURCE.LOGS.PLURAL}}.

ENGLISH: Metallic ore is refined into usable ingots here.
This area stores different kinds of items depending on settings.
Unused items are placed in stockpiles for easy access.
SWEDISH: Oanvända föremål placeras i lager för enkel åtkomst.

ENGLISH: Processes {{SEED.HEMP_SEED}} into textiles for a variety of uses.
Buy and sell items with visiting merchants.

NOTES: Just to describe a light colour

ENGLISH: These are the remains of an item that has completed corroded due to rust.

NOTES: {{VEGETABLE.BARLEY.TOOLTIP}}
ENGLISH: A grain used only in the production of beer. Can be planted in {{SEASON.SPRING}}, {{SEASON.SUMMER}} or {{SEASON.AUTUMN}}.
SWEDISH: Ett korn som endast används vid produktion av öl. Kan planteras i {{SEASON.SPRING}}, {{SEASON.SOMR}} eller {{SEASON.HENT}}

NOTES: {{VEGETABLE.BERSERKER_MUSHROOM.TOOLTIP}}
ENGLISH: A mushroom with a pink-red cap bearing white spots. It has hallucinogenic properties which warriors sometimes use in preparation for battle.
SWEDISH: En svamp med en rosa-röd mössa med vita fläckar. Det har hallucinogena egenskaper som krigare ibland använder för att förbereda sig för strid.

NOTES: {{VEGETABLE.CARROT.TOOLTIP}}
ENGLISH: A hardy root vegetable that survives the {{SEASON.WINTER}} frost. Carrots grow quickly but only produce a small crop. Can be planted in {{SEASON.SPRING}}, {{SEASON.SUMMER}} or {{SEASON.AUTUMN}}.
SWEDISH: En härdig rotgrönsak som överlever {{SEASON.WINTER} -frosten. Morötter växer snabbt men producerar bara en liten gröda. Kan planteras i {{SEASON.SPRING}}, {{SEASON.SOMR}} eller {{SEASON.HENT}}

NOTES: {{VEGETABLE.CORN.TOOLTIP}}
ENGLISH: A cereal grain also known as maize. It produces a bountiful crop but takes around 2 seasons to grow and can not survive {{SEASON.WINTER}}, so it requires planting in early {{SEASON.SPRING}}.
SWEDISH: En spannmålskorn även känd som majs. Den producerar en riklig gröda men tar cirka 2 säsonger att växa och kan inte överleva {{SEASON.WINTER}}, så den kräver plantering i början av {{SEASON.SPRING}}.

NOTES: {{VEGETABLE.DEATH_CAP_MUSHROOM.TOOLTIP}}
ENGLISH: A very poisonous mushroom with a wide, flat cap. Eating even a tiny amount will almost certainly cause poisoning which can lead to death.
SWEDISH: En mycket giftig svamp med en bred, platt keps. Att äta även en liten mängd kommer nästan säkert att orsaka förgiftning som kan leda till döden.

NOTES: {{VEGETABLE.ELFSBANE_MUSHROOM.TOOLTIP}}
ENGLISH: This mushroom has a simple, flavourless taste to most humanoids. Strangely, it tastes absolutely disgusting to elves, who often react with explosive vomiting upon consumption, or in extreme cases, a heart attack.
SWEDISH: Denna svamp har en enkel, smaklös smak för de flesta humanoider. Konstigt nog smakar det helt äckligt för älvor, som ofta reagerar med explosiv kräkningar vid konsumtion eller i extrema fall hjärtinfarkt.

NOTES: {{VEGETABLE.FIST_MUSHROOM.TOOLTIP}}
ENGLISH: A black-blue mushroom with a metallic taste. It is named for a group of bards from the age of darkness.
SWEDISH: En svartblå svamp med metallisk smak. Det är uppkallat efter en grupp bards från mörkrets ålder.

NOTES: {{VEGETABLE.GLOW_MUSHROOM.TOOLTIP}}
ENGLISH: A magic-infused mushroom that gives off light and changes colour with the seasons.
SWEDISH: En magisk svamp som avger ljus och ändrar färg med årstiderna.

ENGLISH: Used to produce rope and fabric after it hsa been processed.

NOTES: {{VEGETABLE.HOPS.TOOLTIP}}
ENGLISH: A flower used for the flavouring of beer. Must be planted in {{SEASON.SPRING}}.
SWEDISH: En blomma som används för smaksättning av öl. Måste planteras i {{SEASON.SPRING}}.

NOTES: {{VEGETABLE.MILTONIA_MUSHROOM.TOOLTIP}}
ENGLISH: Once thought to exist only in the Hudds region, it is now found throughout the world.
SWEDISH: En gång tänkt att existera endast i Hudds-regionen, finns det nu över hela världen.

NOTES: {{VEGETABLE.POTATO.TOOLTIP}}
ENGLISH: A starchy root vegetable which can survive {{SEASON.WINTER}} making it a good choice for most settlements. Can be planted in {{SEASON.SPRING}}, {{SEASON.SUMMER}} or {{SEASON.AUTUMN}}.
SWEDISH: En stärkelserik rotgrönsak som kan överleva {{SEASON.WINTER}} vilket gör det till ett bra val för de flesta bosättningar. Kan planteras i {{SEASON.SPRING}}, {{SEASON.SOMR}} eller {{SEASON.HENT}}

NOTES: {{VEGETABLE.PURPLE_HELMET_MUSHROOM.TOOLTIP}}
ENGLISH: Fat Hat, Plump Turban, Puffy Helmet; This fabled mushroom goes by many names. Legend holds that long ago, many communities of dwarves subsisted entirely on a domesticated strain of this fungus.
SWEDISH: Fat Hat, Plump Turban, Puffy Hjälm; Denna mytomspunna svamp går med många namn. Legenden hävdar att många samhällen av dvärgar levde helt på en domesticerad stam av denna svamp.

NOTES: {{VEGETABLE.ROCIOMYCOTA_MUSHROOM.TOOLTIP}}
ENGLISH: A white and black spotted mushroom. It has been known to affect the appearance of those who ingest it.
SWEDISH: En vit och svart fläckig svamp. Det har varit känt att påverka utseendet hos dem som intar det.

NOTES: {{VEGETABLE.SUNGLOW_MUSHROOM.TOOLTIP}}
ENGLISH: A bright yellow mushroom which glows with the appearance of sunlight. It loses this glow the moment it is harvested.
SWEDISH: En ljusgul svamp som lyser med uppkomsten av solljus. Den förlorar denna glöd när den skördas.

NOTES: {{VEGETABLE.SYRUP_POWDER_MUSHROOM.TOOLTIP}}
ENGLISH: A round orange/yellow mushroom with a white underside. It is said to have been used by mages long ago, but for what purpose, nobody knows.
SWEDISH: En rund orange/gul svamp med vit undersida. Det sägs ha använts av magiker för länge sedan, men för vilket ändamål vet ingen.

NOTES: {{VEGETABLE.TOMATO.TOOLTIP}}
ENGLISH: A plant which grows large red berries often used as a vegetable. Can only be planted in {{SEASON.SPRING}}.
SWEDISH: En växt som växer stora röda bär används ofta som grönsak. Kan endast planteras i {{SEASON.SPRING}}.

NOTES: {{VEGETABLE.WHEAT.TOOLTIP}}
ENGLISH: A cereal grain generally used for the production of bread. It can survive {{SEASON.WINTER}} but takes a while to grow, so it is either planted in {{SEASON.SPRING}} or {{SEASON.AUTUMN}}.
SWEDISH: En spannmålskorn som vanligtvis används för produktion av bröd. Den kan överleva {{SEASON.WINTER}} men tar ett tag att växa, så den är antingen planterad i {{SEASON.SPRING}} eller {{SEASON.HÖSTEN}}.

NOTES: Shrub or bush should do

ENGLISH: Stores harvested fruit and vegetables which can expire.
Stores grains and seeds which will not expire.
Stores tools required for working on jobs.
Stores harvested fruit and vegetables which can expire.
An igneous rock formed by the rapid cooling of lava. Almost all of the volcanic rock in the world is basalt.
SWEDISH: En magmatisk sten som bildas av snabb kylning av lava. Nästan alla vulkaniska stenar i världen är basalt.

ENGLISH: A sedimentary rock mostly made up of the mineral dolomite, so it is also known as dolomite rock.
SWEDISH: En sedimentär bergart som oftast består av mineralet dolomit, så det är också känt som dolomitbergart.

ENGLISH: A blue-hued rock mostly found on an icy island to the north. It has a high iron content.
SWEDISH: En blåaktig sten som oftast finns på en isig ö i norr. Den har en hög järnhalt.

ENGLISH: A common type of igneous rock. It has a large proportion of quartz, making it good for locating certain gemstones.
SWEDISH: En vanlig typ av magmatisk sten. Den har en stor andel kvarts, vilket gör det bra för att lokalisera vissa ädelstenar.

ENGLISH: A lightly-coloured sedimentary rock which makes for a good building material. It is also used as a flux in the production of {{METAL.STEEL.NOUN}}.
SWEDISH: En ljusfärgad sedimentär bergart som ger ett bra byggmaterial. Det används också som ett flöde i produktionen av {{MEAL.STEEL.NOUN}}.

ENGLISH: A metamorphic rock which is used as a high-quality material for sculpture and masonry due to its brilliant appearance.
SWEDISH: En metamorf sten som används som ett högkvalitativt material för skulptur och murverk på grund av dess briljanta utseende.

ENGLISH: A sedimentary rock composed of sand-like fragments.
SWEDISH: En sedimentär bergart bestående av sandliknande fragment.

ENGLISH: A fine-grained sedimentary rock composed of pressurized mud. It can be easily broken into thin layers.
SWEDISH: En finkornig sedimentär bergart bestående av trycksatt lera. Det kan lätt brytas i tunna lager.

ENGLISH: A metamorphic rock that is usually formed out of {{STONE.SHALE.NOUN}}. It is often made into tiles for roofing or writing.
SWEDISH: En metamorf sten som vanligen bildas av {{STONE.SHALE.NOUN}}. Det görs ofta till plattor för takläggning eller skrivning.

ENGLISH: Used to chop down trees. The primary tool of a {{PROFESSION.WOODCUTTER}}.
SWEDISH: Används för att hugga ner träd. Det primära verktyget för en {{PROCUS.WOOKCUTER}}.

ENGLISH: Used to sculpt rock into shape. One of the tools used by a {{PROFESSION.STONEMASON}}.
SWEDISH: Används för att skulptera sten till form. Ett av verktygen som används av en {{PROCUS.STONEMASON}}.

ENGLISH: Used to catch fish from a body of water. The primary tool of a {{PROFESSION.FISHER}}.
SWEDISH: Används för att fånga fisk från en vattenkropp. Det primära verktyget för en {{PROFUS.FISHER}}.

ENGLISH: Used to prepare food, particularly meat.
SWEDISH: Används för att laga mat, särskilt kött.

ENGLISH: Used to bash large items of stone and metal into shape. The primary tool of a {{PROFESSION.BLACKSMITH}}.
SWEDISH: Används för att bash stora föremål av sten och metall i form. Det primära verktyget för en {{PROCUS.BLAKSMITH}}.

ENGLISH: Used to break stone into smaller pieces. The primary tool of a {{PROFESSION.MiNER}}.
SWEDISH: Används för att bryta sten i mindre bitar. Det primära verktyget för en {{Profession.miner}}.

NOTES: A carpenter's plane
A carpenter's plane

ENGLISH: Used to shave wooden furniture and items into shape. The primary tool of a {{PROFESSION.CARPENTER}}.
SWEDISH: Används för att raka trämöbler och föremål i form. Det primära verktyget för en {{PROCUS.CARPENTER}}.

ENGLISH: Used to prepare dough. One of the tools used by a {{PROFESSION.CHEF}}.
SWEDISH: Används för att förbereda deg. Ett av de verktyg som används av en {{PROCUS.CHEF}}.

NOTES: A carpenter's saw
A carpenter's saw

ENGLISH: Used to cut wood into shape. Required for cutting lumber in the {{ROOMS.SAWMILL}}.
SWEDISH: Används för att skära trä i form. Krävs för skärning av virke i {{ROOMS.SAWMILL}}.

ENGLISH: Used to bash small items of stone and metal into shape. One of the tools used by a {{PROFESSION.BLACKSMITH}}.
SWEDISH: Används för att bash små föremål av sten och metall i form. Ett av verktygen som används av en {{PROCUS.BLACKSMITH}}.

NOTES: A blacksmith's tongs
A blacksmith's tongs

ENGLISH: Used to hold extremely hot metal items. Used in the process of smelting metal ore.
SWEDISH: Används för att hålla extremt heta metallföremål. Används vid smältning av metallmalm.

ENGLISH: Minted coins used as a form of currency for trading.
Gems that have been cut and polished to enhance their beauty. Most commonly used as ornamentation.

ENGLISH: This covers the basics of playing.
You should aim to set up a functioning {{ROOMS.SMITHY}} with a {{FURNITURE.FORGE}} provided with fuel and refined metal ore, to produce metal items.
Also, you should move your settlement underground or at least build a roof overhead to protect your Settlers and iron items from the weather.
Rooms with furniture that produce items are controlled using Import and Export Pallets.
Place at least one Import Pallet and Export Pallet in both the Sawmill and Masonry Workshop.
Also, place a Products Stockpile which will hold the items that are produced.
Select each Import and Export Pallet and select the item to be imported or exported from the room.
In the Sawmill, import Logs and export Planks.
In the Masonry Workshop, import Rough stone boulders and export Blocks.
Are you sure you want to end the tutorial?
Click on Rooms and select Farm Plot. They are listed alphabetically.
Drag out 4 separate Farm Plots in a grassy area.
Click on each Farm Plot and select a Crop to be planted.
Press R2 on each Farm Plot and select a Crop to be planted.
Skip Hemp, Barley and Hops for now as these are are used for Textiles and Brewing.
Settlers eat in the Feasting Hall.
The Cauldron furniture for the Feasting Hall is only completed when a Cauldron containing soup is available.
Select Rooms and place a Feasting Hall. Mark a Cauldron to be placed in the Feasting Hall later.
This simple setup will ensure your Settlers have food once the crops are harvested later in the year.
You can also fish from the river or hunt animals once you have set up a military to provide more food.
Crops are harvested in Autumn and should be stored in a Food Stockpile.
To get the most from your crops it is best to produce soup from vegetables or bake bread from grain.
Select Rooms and place a Kitchen. Unlike Farm Plots, most rooms need furniture to function.
The controls in the lower-left corner of the screen are the main way of interacting with the game.
You can assign orders, queue rooms and furniture to be created, and also adjust the priority of tasks.
You can right-click to go back to a previous menu or clear the current selection.
You can press L2 to go back to a previous menu or clear the current selection.
The icons to the left of the time and date are various management and overview screens.
Click on the Minimap to jump to a location
Press R2 with the cursor on the Minimap to jump to a location
Settlers need Food, Drink and Sleep.
For now they can drink from the river and sleep on the ground.
However to eat they must grow crops.
Each Settler can have up to 3 Professions assigned, which determines which jobs they will do.
You can select a Settler to view or change their professions. This can also be done from the Settlers Management screen.
Assign at least 3 Settlers as Farmers. Be sure to also keep some assigned as Haulers as they're responsible for moving items around.

NOTES: Used to show a progress indicator for how many farm plots have a crop selected e.g. 2 of 10 farm plots with a crop assigned
Used to show a progress indicator for how many of a certain profession have been assigned e.g. 2 of 10 farmers assigned
Used to show a progress indicator in the form: 2 of 10 stone blocks
Used to show a progress indicator for a certain number of tiles e.g. 2 of 10 farm plot tiles

ENGLISH: Many items are crafted out of Wooden Planks and Stone Blocks. It's important to maintain a steady supply of these.
Select Orders > Mine. Drag a selection over the mountain area to order your Miners to start mining.
Also select Orders > Chop. Drag a selection over a forested area to order your Woodcutters to start chopping trees.
With all of this in place, your workshops will start producing Wooden Planks and Stone Blocks.
Continue until you have a reasonable supply of Planks and Blocks.
Progress is saved automatically at midnight or when you exit the game.
Progress is saved automatically at midnight each day.
You can also press F5 to Quicksave.
The game is also saved when you quit from the main menu.
Press the WASD keys to move the camera around
Use the Left Stick or D-Pad to move the camera around
Press Q & E or scroll the mouse wheel to zoom
Press L1 and R1 to zoom in and out
Welcome to Mountaincore! This is an Early Access release with gameplay and features still in development.

Your intrepid band of dwarven settlers have chosen this area to found a new colony of their kingdom. Provide food, shelter and prosperity for them and who knows, maybe one day this will be the capital of a kingdom of its own!
It is a good idea to place Stockpiles for your Settlers to place and share items.
Select Rooms and then select Stockpile, then Tools. Drag out a Tools Stockpile in a central location.
You can view the current time, date, weather and control the game's speed here.
Click the icons or press buttons 2, 3 and 4 for increasingly faster speeds
Press R2 on the icons for increasingly faster speeds
Click the icon or press 1 for normal speed
Press R2 over the icon for normal speed
Press space to pause and unpause the game
Press the A button to pause and unpause the game
Click the left-most button to return to the default view mode
Press R2 on the left-most icon to return to the default view mode
Below the time and date are buttons to show different views overlaid onto the game world.
Click one of the other view mode buttons
Press R2 over one of the other view mode buttons
Wooden Planks are produced in a Sawmill by a Woodcutter. Stone Blocks are created in a Masonry Workshop by a Stonemason.
Select Rooms and place a Sawmill and a Masonry Workshop. They both require a crafting station to be constructed.
You can press the R key to Rotate most furniture.
You can press the X button to Rotate most furniture.
Crafting stations have a Crafting button which shows what can be produced.
